cial\" 15 August demonstrations against NNSC:\n\nCOMMENT  South Korea has set a midnight deadline on 13 August for the removal of the commission teams from South Korea.\nmobs may assault the commission compounds if the deadline is not observed.\n\nAlthough earlier plans called for different armed services to assault each of the five commission compounds in South Korea on Liberation Day, 15 August, the army and navy chiefs of staffs have indicated that they would not approve the use of force in such a venture. Police-inspired demonstrations by civilians appear likely to continue, however. Pusan is particularly liable to new violence because of the presence there of a paramilitary force completely loyal to Rhee--General Won Yong-tok's Provost Marshal General Command", "token_count": 127, "token_end_0based": 126, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "far east 1 rhee's police plan special 15 august demonstrations against nnsc comment south korea has set a midnight deadline on 13 august for the removal of the commission teams from south korea mobs may assault the commission compounds if the deadline is not observed although earlier plans called for different armed services to assault each of the five commission compounds in south korea on liberation day 15 august the army and navy chiefs of staffs have indicated that they would not approve the use of force in such a venture police-inspired demonstrations by civilians appear likely to continue however pusan is particularly liable to new violence because of the presence there of a paramilitary force completely loyal to rhee general won yong-tok's provost marshal general command", "unred_source_page": 4}
